[[!taglink Digital_Money]] is the inscription of value on a public ledger.
Digital money is the self-custody of value where legacy banking does not
support this notion. Bitcoin was the first widely available digital currency;
nowadays there are many more coins, tokens, digital assets and real-world assets
available on technology built on the back of Bitcoin.

[[Decentralized_Finance]] is a natural extension of digital money which
democratizes access to financial tools. The simplest tool of DeFi is trustless
lending + borrowing.

